main event: Airmen saw 2 round metallic objects in the sky near Hermanville, Michigan on August 3, 1956.
interesting points: The objects were moving slowly and silently,The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes,The objects were located to the west of the observers,The report was labeled as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation',The sighting was documented in a Project 10073 Record Card.
location: 10 mi N of Hermanville, Michigan, USA
